This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump during the swearing-in ceremony for Alex Azar as the new Secretary of Health and Human Services. The President expressed his confidence in Azar's ability to lower prescription drug prices and tackle the opioid crisis. He also emphasized the need to address the high prices of prescription drugs and the influence of special interests. Azar, in his remarks, thanked the President for the opportunity to serve and pledged to work towards improving the wellbeing and health of all Americans. The President also briefly mentioned his upcoming State of the Union speech, where he plans to discuss topics such as immigration and trade.